reviewText: I didn't realize it when I made this purchase but this is the same concert she performed at Royal Albert Hall .... but the quality of the soundtrack, while good, does not compare to Royal Albert Hall. I now own both and see no reason to have both and, between the two, Live at Royal Albert Hall is much better in all respects.
Arrived ahead of schedule and quality is excellent.

This was a great dvd because it was Adele.

What really impressed me is the way it was produced. It really felt close-up and like she was in a small venue. Very different than the "live at Albert Hall" dvd which I also really like.
